caption: I had the weirdest time here. It was awesome. Expect the unexpected.
They are closed. Mail piling up under the door. Waiter from restaurant next door says they are permanently gone. Another victim of COVID :-/
Karaoke was fun, certainly a dive bar
Strange dive bar, you have to walk down a. Business office hallway to get there. No pitchers if you are going out with a group.
Good prices and a fun dive bar. I am more of a smaller scale karaoke guy, so I may visit but perhaps only during mid week. Also, they keep a juke box with a wide, eclectic selection.
Good basement bar with great happy hour specials

I was told "Come to Karoake night!". The karoake guy only let a few Disgusting. It was like filling out multiple job applications only to have them rejected one by one. And the rest of people around me felt the same way. It should have been called Karoake For Just Us" night. An "in crowd" showed up...knew the DJ and everyone else was finished. It was like they had their own private party and we were the stupid onlookers while we watched them have a good time. Never again. Next time I'll stay home and sing in the shower.
Incredible 💃
Karaoke was a a lot of fun
Great service, good prices, nice friendly environment, friendly staff

It was filled with late teens to early 20 year olds who have probably never experienced a real authentic karaoke bar, otherwise they wouldn't be there. This place was lifeless, dull, and depressing. The drinks were also ridiculously over-priced...like a dressed up dive bar.
Hole
Love this place
(Translated by Google) It's like a party. Karaoke equipment That's right. Underground. Alcohol is not cheap.  (Original) 파티를 하는 곳 같습니다. 노래방 기기도있고 그렇습니다. 지하구요. 술값이 싸지는 않습니다.

Seriously such a good time.!! Visiting from Utah for the week and looking for a fun night and we found it 1000% at this place. Shante at the bar is the sweetest and so friendly! And karaoke ... Omg SOOOO much fun with a great variety list of songs. If you're looking for a place to feel at home when you're out of town, i HIGHLY recommend this place!
Recently bar has had some upgrades. Much  nicer decor, great DJ & staff. Karaoke night was lots of fun!! I'll come back again!
Awful vibe, bad servers, horrible and echoey. Poor selection, even for a beer bar.
My favorite place. Miss Kazi!
Great food go try it out you will love it!!

Recessions has been one of my favorite karaoke bars in the area for years. The owner is all about ensuring his customers are satisfied, bartenders are tentative, and Devon is one of the best KJ’s in the area. Also a plus that they host karaoke Tuesday-Saturday and happy hours until 8! The food is great, best HOMEMADE chicken tenders I’ve had. I also love the mixed crowd, always friendly and chill people here. Definitely recommend to locals and tourists!
Everything you want in a dive. Also seems like this is where the professionals go to kareoke, everyone who sang was amazing - and it was Tuesday.
Drink prices are about DC average but loved the Thursday night karaoke nights!
Love this place. Great staff, prices, atmosphere, etc.
Cheap happy hour! Also, get your sing on with some A1 kareoke!

I have been going to Recessions for nearly 15 years. The definitive dive, they recognize you after a few visits, and for me, they tend to know what I'm getting when I hit the door. The food is minimal, but the king Kong beer mug is huge.  Karaoke is the main fair. I used to hit the Friday night karaoke religiously, now I've started popping up occasionally on Saturdays.
Visited this amazing bar while I was in town for legal reasons. Would come back!
A very happening place in the city, With delicious drink and bar food. Its a place go to with friends after work for a drink. Overall the experience was brilliant. I will stay there again.
I love this bar.  Good food, cheap drinks, and karaoke!  Not your typical basement bar.  Clean and comfortable.

Really nice place to do some singing for free. It has been recently renovated and looks much nicer than it did before. I would give 5 stars if I didn't feel like tha dj skips my songs because they are not " cool" .  but overfull fun and relaxed.

Very mixed crowd, however a more throwback style vibe of a place. Imagine a more 2000's-2009's sort of vibe(in terms of "black" music). However the regulars are pretty friendly, and make the place very easy to kickback and make a new friend especially during happy hour. Food:⭐⭐⭐/5 People:⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Value:⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐(I've seen man charge 4 dollars after ordering 4 drinks.)
Great food. Loved the chicken tenders 💕

Karaoke dive bar in basement of a building with trip hazard multilevel flooring. The staff is very friendly. The group loved the karaoke. They have a pool table. Draft beer of my guest and I tasted like the tap lines needed to be cleaned.
Amazing burgers and just a great place to eat!!

The guy who runs the place is always nice and attentive. Happy hour prices are great.  The food is passable bar food but not great.  They are working on updates but it is bar in the basement - not exactly a luxury venue.  Overall, if you want a drink and some chicken wings for a great price at a dive bar in DC, this is a great choice.  If you want something more, and are willing to pay more, there are better choices.

How do you begin to describe a place like Recessions? A place where giant beers are ridiculously cheap, the carpet was replaced was wood laminate, and the entry way reminds you of the ocean? I know. That word is Superb. Definitely worth a visit, a drink, and a few songs on karaoke.
They are the best!
Not worth the vist...
Food arrived 2 hours late, had less flavor than water. Nothing but texture. NEVER AGAIN!
It was before the Karaoke night set, so there were no crowd. Plus, renovations are being done on the restaurant.
Sign on door says open (permanent engraving), not open! Might be good to redo that sign folks
Generous dive bar in the middle of the city with DJ and dance floor many nights.
Kinda has a dive bar vibe with karaoke.  Quality of singing subject to patrons level of inebriation, so your milage may vary on that front 😉
Incredibly cheap specials and interesting people singing karaoke right through the wee hours of the morning. What's not to like?
great service
Best. Bar. In. DC! This place is an institution. Come and enjoy the King Kong!
Wonderful staff, amazing mozzarella sticks, and an jukebox that can play almost anything you want! The atmosphere is relaxing. Great priced beer and AC without being too cold. I’m coming back!

The DJ was very nice! But no one every came to our table to take our order! We wait over 20 minutes. So we just walked to the bar. The food wasn't that good either.  The atmosphere was nice tho. The music selection needs to be updated like 3 years ago( Afro Latin, & Jamaica , r&b, pop) genres!!!!! I ended up having to just do back on other ppls songs. I had a good time, but that's because I refused to have came all the way out the to have a bad time.  Plus my family was there.
Please avoid Pisco y Nazca... Recessions has Fries... and Kongs. "I used to work construction" - nate french

Despite initially enjoying the atmosphere and drinks prices of this fun karaoke bar, the experience was ruined by the hosts, firstly by singing several slow-paced songs which came off as self-indulgent (there was no lack of singers eager to have a turn), then by singing three extremely long songs to a bride-to-be from a bachelorette party, one of which ended with Host #1 grinding on bride-to-be and looking more like a strip show than a karaoke night. Not fun – it was a public bar, not a private party, and the self-indulgence paired with the creepy behaviour meant my friends and I left after one drink.

I work in the area and have frequently visited this bar on numerous occasions for karaoke and happy hour with my coworkers. We usually have a great time that is until Friday when we all gathered for celebration due to a coworker getting a new job. On Friday, April 12th, our party was enjoying the night when there was a Caucasian guy singing a song with a disrespectful, derogatory word towards blacks (n***a). The gentleman continued to sing the song saying the word until my coworker voiced his opinion. Instead of the DJ stopping the song, my coworker was addressed in a disrespectful way. We decided to leave to the other Caucasian patrons laughing, making comments saying they were glad we were leaving. Needless to say I or my coworkers will not frequent this restaurant/bar ever again and will be spreading the word to others who work in our building. I have never experiences anything like this before.
Super cool hidden gem. Reasonably priced drinks. Nice people. 🥂
Recessions is the greatest bar in DC
Cheap drinks.....very very very sticky floor
Great night spot tucked away in the heart of Washington.  Very nice ambiance and cool Karaoke nights.
I came in a little late for karaoke but still had a great time.  Parking is nonexistent so take the subway.
This place is a dive make no mistake
KARAOKE!!!!
Had a blast at this basement divey bar downtown.
Great spot for karaoke on a weekend! Free karaoke but it’s a LONG wait.
Great drinks...fun place!
Great for karaoke. Sing there once a month on Friday night.
Great happy hour specials
Good beer

Karaoke every night but Monday. Karaoke was below average, it is anarchy and the host and their girl friend sing 25% of the songs. Bartenders made bad jokes and didn't serve 2 of my friends for the first couple hours there. That was weird. However; they have good drink deals on beer. But not the best service. That's all I can say.  I would go again, just don't have high expectations on service.
Fun for karaoke, but the service is horrible. Inexperienced bartenders
Great drinks and Karaoke
Dive.  Dingy.  Depending on your mood and how much you have to drink this place could be fun.   Not pretentious at all.
Nice happy hr

Excellent food quality and taste. It was fun to watch people singing dance on karaoke music. All I feel it was control environment nothing like in pubs drunk people going out of control. All was very jolly people. Love to visit again.
Nice and quiet place if you want to have good conversations with your colleagues. Happy hours rates are just awesome.

Low key spot but good drinks and great happy hour prices with karaoke on some nights. It's not a jumping bar it's just a chill atmosphere in the cut for some drinks and convo. The food is bomb too shout out to the cooks and Manager, he didn't lie when he said I could get a free drink due to miscommunication from prior visit!
French fries are good and they have karoke but atmosphere is a little run down
Fun dive bar great bartender.

Good place. They had cider on their happy hour menu which is great for the people who don't drink beer. Karaoke started at 8pm on Friday when we went there. The music is a little loud before the karaoke started, so we sat at a table farther away from the speakers.
Fair

This is my go to bar in DC, even if it’s more in the ‘dive bar’ category. I lived there for 4 years and this was our spot. No pretense. Cheap prices. Great staff. I don’t want more people to come and ruin it for me but I gotta give credit where it’s due.

A total dive bar with karaoke and pool table. Me and my bunch really had a great times there. It was most of our first time did a karaoke, American style! Yes, center stage in front of others. The drinks are cheap and the foods are ok. The karaoke operator and bartenders are also fun!!!! I will go there again for the karaoke and drinks!

Loved the karaoke and the whole vibe, drinks weren't over the top in pricing, but not the greatest quality. They had karaoke which I love! But the night was ruined when a wedding party walked in and they kicked everyone else who had been waiting off karaoke. It really put a damper on our evening and we decided to head home.
Great happy hour drinks and bites, we had fun times with Karaoke.

Simply put, it's a dive bar with karaoke. I went with a group on a Wednesday night and there were maybe 6 people in the place. It feels bigger than it is with the mirrored back wall. There is one pool table that takes quarters; surprisingly, the pool sticks were in good shape. There are two dartboards, although one is basically useless because of the location of the pool table. It's unpretentious and a good place to stop by for a little karaoke and reasonable drink prices (by D.C. standards).
Kind of a dive but cheap and friendly people
Riz the bartender is a bro. You'll have a lot of fun here.
Quite place, awesome servers, but unexpected entrance. They do Karaoke as well.
Nice dive place in downtown with karaoke, though the low ceilings can cause it to get a bit loud. Nice stone and wood decor, though bathrooms definitely show bar's dive roots.
Karaoke every night and the staff is friendly. Big beers $5 during happy hour and the food hits the spot.
It's a kind a dive bar but fun. Was there for karaoke.  Decent drinks l, not sure about food.
Great  Dive bar
Cocktails were just ok. Probably better to get beer
Best worst bar
Great lower level dive with karaoke! One pool table too!
Nice chill spot I stopped in for a quick bit before hopping on the metro. Certainly felt they had reasonable prices

Echoing others in strange behavior at the karaoke stage  We were the only people at the bar and instead of playing our requests they had the staff sing for 45 minutes? I'm not sure what happened but it seemed like they wanted us to leave at 9 pm on a Saturday. Didn't have food there so I won't leave a 1 star rating
I was part of a group of gay men, and they did not take our requests but gladly sold us drinks. This is DC, and discrimination against the LGBTQ community is real. This establishment is despicable.
It's a dive! Love it! Fyi: the happy hour special is $2 off large mugs, not $5 mugs. SO, a King Kong Bud light is indeed 5 bucks, but the price can run away fast if you get away from domestic swill.

This place is my favorite dive bar in DC. Haji and Riz run the place and have an amazing back story if you want to get them talking ... Great guys. Pool and Karaoke and all of liquor choices you could expect and more.  Watched the Caps win the Stanley Cup here and was so glad for the vibe. Definitely ask for the lamb if you want a real treat to eat. Its full of Indian spices. I haven't tried their lunch buffet but I'm sure its tasty.
This place is a lot of fun. The staff is pretty cool and karaoke rocks!
Karaoke is so much FUN
Karaoke singers seemed to be chosen based on emcee's whim instead of in order of request. There for over 90 mins without anyone from my party being called, and the bar wasn't that full.
Rocky the best bartender!!! It's a hidden gem with the best karaoke
Great food and staff
Went for karaoke, had my entire set skipped so the karaoke host could sing his own set.
Went there for Karaoke.
Will always remember you, take care of you and give you great chicken wings with fun karaoke as a bonus!
A great place to grab a large beer, some good bar food and sing some karaoke.
The best dive bar in DC. Cheap drinks and yummy bar grub.
Dive bar with fun karaoke. Cheap drinks and chill bartenders.
Nice place on weekends nights
The best bar in DC!
A jewel in a hole in a wall
Great burger
In the office/basement of a hotel next to the business center for sending faxes to Carol in accounting. Awesome place?
Great dive bar!
They need to show their hours of the kitchen. Went there and could not eat because the kitchen doesn’t open until 7:00 pm
Great Karaoke!!!
Pool table is in very bad shape. Strong lean, very dirty, expensive. When I went to pay, the worker rang up drinks that were more expensive than what I drank.
Dive bar heaven plus karaoke!
Great for karaoke nights especially if you're looking to get weird. I haven't been here for any other occasion...

A double crown and coke (3 shots and soda) totaled $24. Maybe you pay extra for infuriatingly slow service, actually took about 10 minutes for me to get my drink, and no other drink orders were also being filled by that bartender.  Save yourself the frustration and either go intoxicated or not at all.

I didn't know what was waiting for us as this bar is underground and it was very very dark. Once we entered, surprise! It's a karaoke bar! Luckily, most of the singer sang really well and we really enjoyed the night. Affordable drink is another plus!
Good food, reasonable prices, interesting atmosphere!
Really weird place... you feel like you're in a hotel walking in, but the drink deals are the best in the area (as long as you want a mug of beer).
(Translated by Google) I am hungry  (Original) اني جواعن

I was here for a work HH a couple weeks ago.  It's a smallish basement bar that is a bit cozy.  There were a lot of us so we had a table.  The service was a bit slow, and sometimes drinks or food even failed to arrive, prompting us to ask again.  The drinks were good, but the food and appetizers were pretty plain/basic.  They do have karaoke later on in the evening, but I had already left before they cranked that up.  There is one pool table available, so if you get there early that's a plus.
Down in the deep dark dungeon, karaoke and cheese sticks reign supreme.
Always a good time here. The best kept secret for happy hour in DC!  A nice underground hideaway good people food and drinks at a reasonable price!
It's an underground dump bar. It smells like a sewer. Stay away!
The great service
I've had countless outing with friends here for good food, drinks, and karaoke!
Dive bar with great happy hour prices
Excellent prices for Happy Hour beer. Nice karaoke and good seating.
Best chicken in all neighborhood. Great atmosphere and people. Really cool place and prices.
I quite and reasonably priced dive bar.  Met my every expectation.   Don't go here expecting anything upscale or fancy.
This place feels like it never left the eighties and has karaoke on Friday nights.  What's not to love?

Drinks were cheap. In price AND quality. 20mins after finishing my drink I had a TERRIBLE headache. 20mins after THAT I was dead sober again! Bartender had a horrendous attitude. Geez LOUISE! Never again.
It looks like a dive (which I love) but the prices are not dive prices.  They would have to lower prices $1- $2 each drink.
Dungeon bar with Karaoke.  Oddly addictive.
This place said they were closed at 749pm...during a bar crawl but online said it's open until 12am

One of the few legitimate dive bars in DC.  Cheap beer, cheap drinks, questionable bar food, and no windows.  It's in a basement, shared with a hotel business center.  If you're looking for someplace fancy to take a date, don't come here.  If you're looking to burn some hours away with some friends, it's a great location.  They've got pool and Big Buck Hunter, an internet-enabled jukebox, and host karaoke some nights as well.  Saturday night hosts Spellbound DC (local goth / industrial scene).

A great local dive bar!  Dinner and a 25oz beer was a whopping $15.  I'm not sure why people come here and leave poor reviews if basement bars aren't their thing but I assure you the atmosphere is just fine for being surrounded by bars and restaurants in the opposite category.  Service was excellent and professional but what really stood out was their offer to refill my water bottle before we left.  A simple gesture but anyone who pays attention to detail certainly reflects in other aspects.  The only complaint is that I won't find the same quality gyro in Cincinnati without paying double the price.
A dump dive bar, watered down drinks, dark and dusty basement.
Fun semi-dive bar with cheap drinks and karaoke.
Love the space. Cheap beer and karaoke
Cheap beer, cheap food and Karaoke. What more do you need?
Great place for Happy Hour
Relaxed bar
A dive bar that doesn't try to be more than it is. If you're looking for a local watering hole, this is a great place for a drink.
This bar has a very divey feel, being in a basement. The service is always great and the happy hour prices are generally pretty good!

Love the new lunch they have setup. I have been going here for some years now for happy hours and lunch. The food and prices are great.  The new lunch buffet is really good, the curry is really good with rice or bread and the price is cheap for all you can eat. I met the chef today as he was setting up the bread, really nice well dressed clean cut team they have over there.  highly recommend this place for lunch and happy hour.  Ask for Kazi, he makes the best drinks.

Basement bar, so you have to know to expect a certain dive feel. This place accepts and embraces what they are. Cheap drinks, good food, and an eclectic mix of clientel. If you want a classy upscale bar... this isn't for you. If you want cold cheap beer and drunken karaoke, bring your friends and have a blast. I'll probably see you there.
Very bad service won't go back ever.
Always friendly, and great prices.

This place clearly prides itself on its lackluster, no frills atmosphere. Some people love it. I, myself, really wish they had some sort of background music on all the time instead of a pay-to-play jukebox. If you do decide to use the jukebox, beware that it will only play certain songs. I paid for six different songs and it only played three of them. I guess it just knows what it likes :]

What can you say about Recessions? It's a divey, dark bar in the basement of an office building....and it's fantastic! If you're looking for a cheap bar with lots of character, diverse clientele, and a downtown location...Recessions is an amazing choice. The food and drinks are good and incredibly cheap; the Friday karaoke raucous and wonderful; the bartenders friendly and efficient. It's simply a great, under-the-radar, CHEAP bar in an otherwise pricey and pretentious neighborhood.

I secretly love Recessions. It is so perfect and cheap! On Fridays they have karaoke, which is hilarious. Really, when you want to hang out with friends and just drink, why does it matter what the bar looks like? Their appetizers are perfectly adequate, and the service is fine -- attentive, but not overly friendly or anything.
Dingy undergrad bar.

SO much fun. If you imagine a classic dive, Recessions embodies almost all of it. Just now becoming popular with the hipster crowd, this hole in the basement bar serves its purpose well. Cheap huge beers, relatively good food (chicken fingers were great bar fodder), and an entertaining crowd. Going on karaoke night is advised!!

The bartenders and servers are friendly for 1. It's a real chill environment, you don't have to worry about some crazy instance happening. It's even comfortable to go alone and you dont have to worry about some strange character hanging outside. I like it, its def my first choice bar when I'm in the area
